1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,669
[Alice] <i>Erica, something happened.</i>

2
00:00:04,754 --> 00:00:06,506
[Annette] <i>Althea, don't give up, okay?</i>

3
00:00:06,589 --> 00:00:08,425
[Edong]<i> I didn't do this. I didn't!</i>

4
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:09,759
[Edward]<i> I know your story, Edong.</i>

5
00:00:09,843 --> 00:00:12,303
<i>Everything will be</i>
<i>easier if we work together.</i>

6
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:14,472
<i>- You should just die!</i>
- [Edward grunting]

7
00:00:14,556 --> 00:00:16,766
<i>Your father is back here in Amurao.</i>

8
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:19,269
<i>You need something from me.</i>
<i>In exchange for what, Attorney?</i>

9
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:21,146
<i>Your cooperation in catching Edong.</i>

10
00:00:21,229 --> 00:00:24,357
<i>You don't defend</i>
<i>people like Crisanto Santiago.</i>

11
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:27,569
<i>Whether we like it or not,</i>
<i>we need him to get Edong out of hiding!</i>

12
00:00:27,652 --> 00:00:30,447
<i>It is not the police</i>
<i>who will make him pay.</i>

13
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:31,698
<i>It should be me alone.</i>

14
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,908
<i>Auntie! You should've called me.</i>

15
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:34,909
<i>There…</i>

16
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:46,588
[sinister music playing]

17
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:49,883
No… [gasps]

18
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:51,634
No.

19
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,513
[Edward] I really should have…

20
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:58,641
fixed the cabinet door.

21
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:03,188
[sinister music continues]

22
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:05,523
[Alice crying]

23
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:06,691
It was you?

24
00:01:10,445 --> 00:01:11,488
It was you.

25
00:01:14,365 --> 00:01:17,786
I didn't just disappear
from the market that day.

26
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,414
You lured me.

27
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,043
[sobs] What did you do to me?

28
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:30,423
Who are you?!

29
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:32,759
[breathing heavily]

30
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:37,639
[sinister music continues]

31
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:45,647
[theme music playing]

32
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:59,512
[suspenseful music playing]

33
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:14,611
[vendor] <i>Balut! Balut! Balut.</i>

34
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:16,946
[vendor] Boss, <i>balut?</i>

35
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:22,368
Thanks, man. <i>Balut!</i>

36
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:24,579
<i>Balut!</i>

37
00:03:24,662 --> 00:03:30,001
[suspenseful music continues]

38
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,130
<i>Balut!</i>

39
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:36,216
[phone buzzing]

40
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,510
"Officer Ramos: E"

41
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:42,013
All units, standby. Santo, driver's seat.

42
00:03:42,096 --> 00:03:43,640
Kristo, open the van.

43
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:45,183
Keep your hands on your holster!

44
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,813
[Locsin] Kristo, target at 6 o'clock!

45
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:52,440
He's armed! Cover!

46
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:54,234
[ominous music playing]

47
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:55,526
[officer] Put that down!

48
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:57,445
Get down! Down!

49
00:03:58,029 --> 00:04:00,657
- [Lucas] Don't hurt him!
- Get down! Get down!

50
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:02,742
[gun thuds]

51
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:06,287
- [Lucas] Don't hurt him!
- [officer] Get down! Get down!

52
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:09,415
[ominous music intensifies]

53
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:11,918
[officer] Negative!

54
00:04:12,001 --> 00:04:15,922
[music turns tense]

55
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:17,715
[Locsin] Unit Delta, 9 o'clock!

56
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:23,179
Sir, he's not the target!

57
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:26,933
[officer] These bastards!
They're toying with us!

58
00:04:27,475 --> 00:04:29,519
- [officer] Sir! Stop!
- [Locsin] Adjust! Split in two!

59
00:04:29,602 --> 00:04:30,812
[officer] Stop! Get down!

60
00:04:32,563 --> 00:04:34,857
- Negative, sir!
- [officer] Stop!

61
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,902
- [officer] Put that down!
- [Locsin] Split in two… Shit!

62
00:04:40,446 --> 00:04:41,281
[officer] Hey!

63
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:46,202
[tense music continues]

64
00:04:50,915 --> 00:04:52,208
There! At the side!

65
00:04:53,918 --> 00:04:56,004
- [officer 1] Stop him!
- [officer 2] Get down!

66
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,673
- [officer] Get down!
- [music ends]

67
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:03,803
[foreboding music playing]

68
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:06,014
- [man grunts]
- [officer] Get down!

69
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:07,640
[body thuds]

70
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:10,727
[Lucas] Huh…
What the hell, This isn't my brother!

71
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:14,397
[foreboding music continues]

72
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,190
- [blows landing]
- [body thuds]

73
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:17,859
- [officer groans]
- There's Edong!

74
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,448
[Crisanto] Damn you, you bastard!

75
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,826
Edong! Edong, get out of there!

76
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:28,745
[Erica] Edong!

77
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:31,748
- This isn't the right time.
- [Erica] Edong, get out! Edong!

78
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,416
- [flesh squelches]
- [groans]

79
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,335
Edong, get out of there!

80
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:36,502
[Crisanto] groans]

81
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:37,962
[car engine rumbling]

82
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:38,796
Edong!

83
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,631
- [tires screeching]
- No!

84
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:43,092
[gunshots]

85
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:50,141
[police sirens blaring]

86
00:05:50,224 --> 00:05:51,684
[Delos Santos] Did Edong pay you?

87
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,227
You're all so young,

88
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,730
yet you're helping that criminal!

89
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:57,857
He doesn't need to pay us!

90
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:00,443
All of Amurao failed him…

91
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:02,445
But we won't.

92
00:06:02,987 --> 00:06:05,948
He is us. And we are Edong!

93
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:08,993
[dramatic music sting]

94
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:12,622
<i>Damn, dude.</i>
<i>They even held a press conference.</i>

95
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:15,333
<i>But did you hear even one apology?</i>

96
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:16,542
<i>No, right?</i>

97
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:18,753
<i>But even if</i>
<i>they say a million apologies…</i>

98
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,379
<i>They shouldn't be forgiven!</i>

99
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:25,134
<i>It's like they're saying it was okay</i>
<i>when those cops shot my father!</i>

100
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:27,386
<i>They even made him</i>
<i>out to be a drug addict!</i>

101
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,847
<i>The hell…</i>
<i>He didn't even know how to smoke!</i>

102
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:33,810
<i>So now, all of</i>
<i>Amurao thinks I'm a druggie!</i>

103
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:35,269
<i>- These bastards…</i>
<i>- What about when</i>

104
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:38,481
<i>I just reported</i>
<i>the Mayor's scumbag son shoplifting…</i>

105
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:41,734
<i>When, suddenly,</i>
<i>he's saying he saw me stealing!</i>

106
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:45,238
<i>If you're poor,</i>
<i>you're instantly sentenced.</i>

107
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:46,864
<i>But if you're rich…</i>

108
00:06:46,948 --> 00:06:49,826
<i>If you make a mistake,</i>
<i>you can just hold a press con!</i>

109
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:52,578
<i>If you're poor, even if you just breathe…</i>

110
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,205
<i>You're a criminal!</i>

111
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:57,959
[Edong sighs] <i>Don't just accept that.</i>

112
00:06:59,335 --> 00:07:02,588
<i>Even if you're poor, you have to breathe.</i>

113
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,298
[unsettling music playing]

114
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:07,468
<i>Get out of the box they caged you in.</i>

115
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:10,680
<i>Don't get carried away, don't drown…</i>

116
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,266
<i>in their judgment.</i>

117
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:15,893
<i>Breathe.</i>

118
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:19,897
[unsettling music continues]

119
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:24,152
<i>Don't die,</i>

120
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:30,158
<i>just to prove</i>
<i>that their lives are more important.</i>

121
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,077
<i>Breathe.</i>

122
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,872
<i>Live.</i>

123
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:41,127
[unsettling music continues]

124
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,295
<i>You…</i>

125
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:44,046
<i>are not…</i>

126
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:45,923
<i>alone.</i>

127
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:49,552
<i>And I hope…</i>

128
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,431
<i>I'm not alone either.</i>

129
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:58,728
[unsettling music continues]

130
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:00,021
<i>I…</i>

131
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,273
<i>need you.</i>

132
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:09,530
[followers chant]
Justice! Justice! Justice!

133
00:08:09,614 --> 00:08:15,203
Justice! Justice! Justice! Justice!

134
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:21,959
Justice! Justice!
Justice! Justice! Justice!

135
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:26,506
Justice! Justice! Justice!

136
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:32,011
Justice! Justice! Justice! Justice!

137
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:36,349
[Alice breathing shakily]

138
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:38,601
[music becomes sinister]

139
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:41,187
Don't look at me like that, Alice.

140
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,231
[Alice crying]

141
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:45,107
You know that you're special to me.

142
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:47,735
You are my favorite.

143
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:50,530
You woke me.

144
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:52,198
[sobbing]

145
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:53,574
And because of you…

146
00:08:54,742 --> 00:08:56,536
I discovered who I really am.

147
00:08:56,619 --> 00:09:01,165
[sinister music continues]

148
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,253
<i>- Heart, you okay?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

149
00:09:06,629 --> 00:09:08,256
<i>Dad. Yes.</i>

150
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:11,008
<i>Hi, Ma. Thank you.</i>

151
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:15,680
[sinister music continues]

152
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:19,016
[music fades]

153
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,434
<i>My condolences, Edward.</i>

154
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:22,603
<i>Everyone's sad</i>
<i>about your father's passing.</i>

155
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,230
<i>Thank you.</i>

156
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,858
<i>Shouldn't you be taking a break?</i>

157
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,611
<i>They still asked you to come?</i>

158
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,407
<i>Are you sure about Christina, Edward?</i>

159
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:36,576
<i>You took care of your father for years.</i>

160
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,744
<i>The same thing will</i>
<i>happen to you with Christina.</i>

161
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:41,163
<i>You'll take care of</i>
<i>her the rest of your life!</i>

162
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:45,167
<i>My cousin knows</i>
<i>what he's doing, Miss Nessa.</i>

163
00:09:45,793 --> 00:09:48,170
<i>Let him choose who he wants to care for.</i>

164
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:52,091
<i>And let's not make it a hobby</i>
<i>to interfere with other people's lives.</i>

165
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:57,388
<i>I'm just saying the truth,</i>
<i>which you should be doing, Mike!</i>

166
00:09:57,471 --> 00:10:01,309
<i>You're like a brother to Edward.</i>
<i>You're his only family.</i>

167
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:07,481
<i>Miss Nessa really hasn't changed.</i>

168
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,025
[Susan] <i>It's just that you're too kind.</i>

169
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,943
<i>You've been like that since we were kids.</i>

170
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,404
[Mike] <i>You're getting scolded again!</i>

171
00:10:13,487 --> 00:10:16,032
<i>You're making my wife angry again!</i>

172
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:18,826
<i>She might just punch you again.</i>

173
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:22,538
<i>Mama, don't get mad at Uncle Edward.</i>

174
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,790
[Susan] <i>I'm not mad</i>
<i>at Uncle Edward, my dear.</i>

175
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,417
<i>Your Papa's just joking.</i>

176
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:30,713
[chuckles]

177
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:36,135
<i>Alice is really my defender.</i>

178
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:37,219
[chuckles]

179
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:39,513
<i>Ah.</i>

180
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:43,809
<i>- Thank you!</i>
<i>- You're welcome!</i>

181
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:45,728
- [Susan] <i>You're really…</i>
- [Mike chuckles]

182
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,772
[Mike] <i>Oh, Edward,</i>
<i>where should we put this?</i>

183
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:50,983
<i>Ah! You should list</i>
<i>it down with Christina first.</i>

184
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,693
<i>- Okay, all right.</i>
<i>- All right. Okay.</i>

185
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:55,112
[unsettling music playing]

186
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:56,197
[Mike] <i>Hello, hi.</i>

187
00:10:57,114 --> 00:11:00,326
[Edward] I tried
to stop what I felt for you…

188
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,246
that feeling of wanting you to be mine…

189
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:06,957
…because you're my cousin's daughter.

190
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:10,544
[unsettling music continues]

191
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,004
But on that day…

192
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:15,716
I saw you.

193
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:23,140
[music becomes foreboding]

194
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:49,083
[foreboding music continues]

195
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:52,628
[young Alice] <i>Uncle!</i>
<i>Can I stop hiding now?</i>

196
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,797
<i>Yes, Alice. We're here.</i>

197
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,799
<i>We'll wait for your mom inside, okay?</i>

198
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:00,428
<i>Mama's coming here?</i>

199
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:04,265
[foreboding music continues]

200
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:06,475
<i>Go on, finish that. We'll go inside.</i>

201
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:11,397
[ominous music sting]

202
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,606
[Edward] <i>Come, Alice.</i>

203
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:14,859
<i>Let's go to your grandpa's house.</i>

204
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:19,780
[foreboding music continues]

205
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:30,332
<i>Stay here, okay?</i>

206
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:36,088
[foreboding music continues]

207
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:48,309
<i>Alice, we're going to play a game, okay?</i>

208
00:12:48,392 --> 00:12:51,395
<i>Just follow along</i>
<i>with what Uncle says, okay?</i>

209
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:56,192
[foreboding music continues]

210
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,994
<i>I want my Mama.</i>

211
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:09,413
<i>Ah… Just a second.</i>

212
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:12,583
[ropes creaking]

213
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:23,594
[camera clicks]

214
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:29,016
[young Alice] <i>I want my Mama…</i>

215
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:31,018
[Edward chuckles]

216
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:34,855
[camera clicks]

217
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:36,524
<i>Mama…</i>

218
00:13:38,442 --> 00:13:39,360
[Edward scoffs]

219
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:44,448
[foreboding music continues]

220
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:49,119
<i>Alice, here. Drink this.</i>

221
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:52,498
<i>Here. You like this, right?</i>

222
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:54,375
[glass shatters]

223
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,210
[Edward] <i>Look at what you did!</i>

224
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,711
- [glass shatters]
<i>- Quiet!</i>

225
00:13:57,795 --> 00:13:59,505
<i>I am not cheating on you!</i>

226
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,048
<i>- Please just listen to me.</i>
- [Alice grunts]

227
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:02,424
[Edward] <i>Shut up!</i>

228
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,885
<i>Shut up and keep quiet!</i>

229
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:07,179
<i>- Shut up!</i>
- [phone ringing]

230
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:09,014
<i>You would have already been mine…</i>

231
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:11,850
<i>But your father just had to intervene!</i>

232
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:17,189
[ringing continues]

233
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:19,108
[Edward] <i>Mike isn't just a cousin.</i>

234
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,319
<i>He's also a dear friend.</i>

235
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:25,447
[ringing continues]

236
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,075
<i>When I saw him calling me that day,</i>

237
00:14:28,158 --> 00:14:29,535
<i>I suddenly felt terrified.</i>

238
00:14:29,618 --> 00:14:31,078
- [young Alice crying]
<i>- Alice, stop crying.</i>

239
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:35,332
- [ringing continues]
- [Alice continues sobbing]

240
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:36,625
<i>Don't cry!</i>

241
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,795
[wailing] <i>Mama!</i>

242
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:41,171
<i>Shut up!</i>

243
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:42,882
<i>Be quiet!</i>

244
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:46,969
- [ringing continues]
- [crying faintly]

245
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,432
<i>Stay right there.</i>

246
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:54,977
[ringing continues]

247
00:14:55,060 --> 00:15:00,107
[wailing] <i>Mama! Mama!</i>

248
00:15:03,527 --> 00:15:05,696
[foreboding music continues]

249
00:15:05,779 --> 00:15:06,780
<i>Cousin.</i>

250
00:15:07,114 --> 00:15:09,199
[Mike] <i>Cousin, Alice is missing!</i>

251
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,368
<i>Missing?</i>

252
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:15,122
<i>Yes! We already reported it to the police.</i>
<i>We're going to look for her now.</i>

253
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:18,167
<i>I'll help.</i>

254
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:22,671
[wailing] <i>Ma!</i>

255
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:29,011
After I talked to Cousin…

256
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:32,765
I didn't push through with
what I was gonna do to you.

257
00:15:32,848 --> 00:15:35,809
[music becomes unsettling]

258
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:36,810
However…

259
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,145
You knew…

260
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:40,105
[sobs]

261
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:41,607
The things I'd done to you.

262
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,277
I couldn't let you leave alive.

263
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,238
You'll tell your father about it.

264
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:50,407
You'll expose everything I did.

265
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:52,368
My life will be ruined!

266
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:56,956
[wailing] <i>Mama! Papa! Help!</i>

267
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,918
<i>Alice, shut up!</i>

268
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:05,923
[panicked breaths]

269
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,175
<i>Be quiet.</i>

270
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:09,927
[young Alice crying]

271
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,095
<i>Be quiet!</i>

272
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:14,556
<i>Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!</i>

273
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:19,853
[panicked breaths]

274
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:20,813
<i>Stop crying!</i>

275
00:16:20,896 --> 00:16:23,065
[crying] <i>Mama! Papa!</i>

276
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:25,401
[whispers] <i>Quiet.</i>

277
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:29,989
[Edward's father]
<i>You're no different from me!</i>

278
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:32,449
<i>You'll be a demon too just like me!</i>

279
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:37,329
[Edward] But I don't
want to be like my father.

280
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,125
For so many years, he hurt me!

281
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:42,501
Abused me!

282
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:45,629
[crying]

283
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:48,882
I still tried to get my soul to salvation.

284
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:53,512
[unsettling music continues]

285
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:59,309
And so I let you live.

286
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:03,188
I gave you back to them.

287
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,275
Even if meant that…

288
00:17:07,192 --> 00:17:09,611
Everyone would find out about my secret.

289
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,448
I was certain then.

290
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:15,743
That my life is ruined!

291
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:22,833
- [eerie music playing]
- [church bell ringing]

292
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,045
<i>I'm not like you!</i>

293
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:34,303
[phone ringing]

294
00:17:39,349 --> 00:17:43,479
[sniffling]

295
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:47,566
[Mike] <i>Hello, Cousin?</i>

296
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:49,401
<i>We found Alice!</i>

297
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,532
<i>How is she?</i>

298
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:58,827
<i>Does she know what happened to her?</i>

299
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,830
<i>Not yet. </i>[sighs heavily]

300
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:03,665
<i>We keep asking her, but…</i>

301
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,918
<i>She doesn't know.</i>

302
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,377
<i>She couldn't tell us anything.</i>

303
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:12,800
[eerie music continues]

304
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:14,676
[Mike] <i>According to the police…</i>

305
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:18,889
<i>Alice may have just strayed</i>
<i>far from Susan that's why she got lost.</i>

306
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:21,683
<i>As for her wounds,</i>

307
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,353
<i>it's possible she got</i>
<i>them from wandering around.</i>

308
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,608
<i>They also said that…</i>

309
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:32,653
<i>If Alice got kidnapped,</i>

310
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:36,824
<i>it's impossible to find</i>
<i>her within 10 mere hours.</i>

311
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:40,911
<i>I'm so nervous, Cousin.</i>

312
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:43,455
<i>Because Alice can't remember anything.</i>

313
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:47,876
<i>We want her to see</i>
<i>a doctor just to be sure.</i>

314
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:50,003
<i>She's here.</i>

315
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:56,218
[tense music playing]

316
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:09,148
<i>Uncle Edward!</i>

317
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:13,318
[Edward] It was a miracle, Alice.

318
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:16,238
You didn't remember a thing!

319
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,241
[laughing]

320
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:20,826
I was saved!

321
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:22,828
[sobbing] A miracle?

322
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,539
A miracle?!

323
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:28,584
I was-- I was traumatized for years!

324
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:31,587
I buried it in my brain.

325
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:36,550
I buried it.
It-- it eventually crawled its way out.

326
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:41,263
I don't know what's going on with me.

327
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:45,184
I even-- I even accused
my husband of abusing me!

328
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:48,145
I thought I was going insane!

329
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:49,938
No, Alice.

330
00:19:50,647 --> 00:19:52,107
It was a miracle!

331
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,736
It was a miracle, Alice!

332
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:57,905
And because of it,

333
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:00,949
I got close to your parents.

334
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:03,702
[sinister music playing]

335
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:05,204
To Cousin,

336
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,456
to Susan,

337
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,417
and most of all…

338
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:15,797
To you.

339
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:26,475
[crying]

340
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:29,019
After what happened, I tried to change.

341
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:33,649
I tried not to listen
to the part of myself

342
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,817
that I inherited from my father.

343
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:39,488
I had his house demolished.

344
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:42,824
I proposed to your Auntie Christina,
I married her!

345
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,451
And I hoped…

346
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:47,496
That my life would be better.

347
00:20:47,579 --> 00:20:48,705
[crying]

348
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:49,998
Me…

349
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:51,959
But in the end…

350
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,087
I still couldn't control myself.

351
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:57,464
[sinister music continues]

352
00:20:57,547 --> 00:21:04,429
[children chattering indistinctly]

353
00:21:06,098 --> 00:21:07,474
[child 1] <i>Tag, you're it!</i>

354
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,227
[child 2] <i>Tag, you're it!</i>

355
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:13,230
[Edward] Ella.

356
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:15,816
She was my first.

357
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,610
What I didn't get to do to you,

358
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:20,779
I did to her instead.

359
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:25,325
What was difficult with you,
was so easy with her.

360
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:28,620
It's because no one was stopping me.

361
00:21:28,704 --> 00:21:30,330
Even Christina,

362
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:33,959
she was never a hindrance to me.

363
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:37,838
That's why I chose her.

364
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:40,841
Because she is easily fooled!

365
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:43,552
- [leaves rustling]
- [sinister music continues]

366
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,095
- [rustling]
- [Edward breathing heavily]

367
00:21:45,178 --> 00:21:46,430
[Edward grunts]

368
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:53,437
[breathing heavily]

369
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:59,568
[sinister music continues]

370
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:03,780
- [Edward] But Amurao?
- [Edward grunting]

371
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:05,490
It's way too small!

372
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:09,286
The people here are
too nosy and meddlesome!

373
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:14,624
[buyer 1] <i>She's been missing for weeks…</i>

374
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,710
<i>Isn't she dead already?</i>

375
00:22:16,793 --> 00:22:18,920
[vendor] <i>The parents couldn't accept it.</i>

376
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:21,882
<i>I heard that they were</i>
<i>going to ask for help.</i>

377
00:22:21,965 --> 00:22:24,343
<i>Even if they reach the Malacañang!</i>

378
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:28,764
[buyer 2] <i>An outsider did this for sure.</i>

379
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:30,849
[buyer 3] <i>But what if they aren't?</i>

380
00:22:30,932 --> 00:22:34,061
<i>Oh my god, there's a monster in this town?</i>

381
00:22:34,144 --> 00:22:37,606
<i>My husband and I are</i>
<i>gonna help hunting it down!</i>

382
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:39,066
<i>We have a kid!</i>

383
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:40,192
[buyer 3] <i>Yeah.</i>

384
00:22:40,275 --> 00:22:45,822
[sinister music continues]

385
00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:48,283
[Edward] So I thought…

386
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:52,913
I shouldn't take what I need from Amurao.

387
00:22:55,832 --> 00:22:57,417
And I was right, Alice.

388
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,004
It really worked better for me.

389
00:23:02,089 --> 00:23:03,548
Everything became easier.

390
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:06,760
Whenever the church group

391
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:10,806
asks me to give
donations to various places,

392
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:13,975
that where I find my little Marys.

393
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:16,478
[scoffs, sniffles]

394
00:23:16,561 --> 00:23:19,106
I hid and buried them in different places.

395
00:23:19,648 --> 00:23:20,774
[sighs in disgust]

396
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:22,776
And no one knows that.

397
00:23:23,902 --> 00:23:25,445
They're all mine.

398
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:27,030
[sobs]

399
00:23:29,157 --> 00:23:30,492
Except for Ella.

400
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:34,037
Because that damn
Edong ruined what's mine!

401
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:37,541
- [scoffs]
- He tainted my Ella!

402
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:40,669
[crying] Your little Marys?

403
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:44,798
[scoffs] Do you even hear yourself, Uncle?

404
00:23:44,881 --> 00:23:46,967
They are children! Children!

405
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:49,553
You had nothing to do with them.

406
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:53,223
If it weren't for you, they would
still be with their parents right now.

407
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,643
They deserve to grow up safe and loved.

408
00:23:57,394 --> 00:23:59,479
They deserve their futures!

409
00:23:59,563 --> 00:24:01,606
[ominous music playing]

410
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,358
They didn't deserve to be touched!

411
00:24:03,441 --> 00:24:05,902
Touched and abused by you!

412
00:24:08,196 --> 00:24:09,739
You're a monster.

413
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,867
God, you're a monster!

414
00:24:13,201 --> 00:24:16,621
How many children did you hurt? How many?!

415
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:19,916
The world is just merely
paying back what it owes me!

416
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:23,670
I have suffered by the hands of my father

417
00:24:23,753 --> 00:24:25,213
for so many years, Alice!

418
00:24:25,881 --> 00:24:28,508
And you don't know how much it hurts!

419
00:24:28,592 --> 00:24:30,343
How hard it was!

420
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:32,721
You don't know anything!

421
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:36,641
[ominous music continues]

422
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:41,271
My luck changed when he died.

423
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:43,982
The world gave back

424
00:24:45,525 --> 00:24:47,277
everything it took from me.

425
00:24:50,113 --> 00:24:51,907
You forgot what I did to you.

426
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:56,244
I didn't get caught
for what I did to Ella.

427
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:00,081
That's why Mike died all of a sudden

428
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:05,337
before he could tell
my secrets to everyone!

429
00:25:07,297 --> 00:25:08,381
What?

430
00:25:08,465 --> 00:25:12,594
[dramatic music playing]

431
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:14,471
Mike found out what I was doing.

432
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:19,893
Mike found out what I did to you.

433
00:25:21,645 --> 00:25:24,105
[crying] What did you do to him?

434
00:25:28,151 --> 00:25:30,028
What did you do to him?!

435
00:25:30,111 --> 00:25:32,781
What did you do to him! [echoes]

436
00:25:34,324 --> 00:25:35,450
[young Alice] <i>Papa!</i>

437
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:37,035
- [Mike screams]
- [truck horn honking]

438
00:25:37,118 --> 00:25:39,120
- [metal crashing]
- [glass shattering]

439
00:25:41,122 --> 00:25:42,582
[dramatic music sting]

440
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:44,918
[Beth] <i>Erica still hasn't contacted us!</i>

441
00:25:45,001 --> 00:25:47,003
<i>Alice should've been</i>
<i>here a long time ago too!</i>

442
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:48,755
<i>- Where is she?</i>
<i>- At Uncle Edward's.</i>

443
00:25:48,838 --> 00:25:50,882
<i>You're a monster! You're a monster!</i>

444
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:51,967
<i>Help!</i>

445
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,219
<i>We were following him</i>
<i>but we lost him along the way.</i>

446
00:25:54,302 --> 00:25:56,888
<i>- The police lost him too.</i>
<i>- Where else could he take your father?</i>

447
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:58,139
<i>- To my mother!</i>
- [Crisanto grunts]

448
00:25:58,223 --> 00:26:00,558
[Edong] <i>I didn't</i>
<i>bring you here for forgiveness.</i>

449
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:02,811
<i>I brought you here to pay.</i>

450
00:26:02,894 --> 00:26:04,312
[Crisanto] <i>If your mother was still alive,</i>

451
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:08,275
<i>she would've despised you</i>
<i>because you've become so much like me!</i>

452
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:10,568
<i>Shut the hell up!</i>

453
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:11,611
[gunshot]
